## Project structure

Repos vary by scope. Use the layout that matches the project; document the actual tree in [[architecture/repo-layout]].

### A — Workflows-only repo

```
repo-root/
├── README.md
├── package.json                 ← optional: devDeps, test script for lib/
├── workflows/
│   ├── *.json                   ← exported workflows (no secrets)
│   └── README.md
├── lib/                         ← optional: shared JS/TS for Code nodes
├── tests/
├── scripts/
│   └── run.ps1
├── credentials/                 ← EMPTY in git (.gitkeep only)
├── .n8n/                        ← runtime data (gitignored)
└── docs/vault/
```

### B — Community / custom node package

Follow [n8n community package conventions](https://docs.n8n.io/integrations/creating-nodes/build/):

```
repo-root/
├── package.json                 ← n8n.nodes, n8n.credentials, n8n.npm.packageName
├── tsconfig.json
├── gulpfile.js
├── nodes/
│   └── <NodeName>/
│       ├── <NodeName>.node.ts   ← INodeType
│       └── <node>.svg
├── credentials/                 ← ICredentialType (*.credentials.ts) if needed
├── dist/                        ← build output (gitignored or published)
├── test/ or __tests__/          ← jest unit tests
└── docs/vault/
```

### C — Monorepo (workflows + packages)

Keep `workflows/` and `packages/n8n-nodes-*/` siblings; document cross-references in MOC.

### D — Multi-program monorepo (this repo)

```
workflows/
├── complaints/
├── servicedesk/
├── daily-checks/
├── daily-ops/
└── _shared/                 ← sub-workflows
lib/
├── core/ schemas/ simulators/
├── complaints/ servicedesk/ daily-checks/ daily-ops/
fixtures/ prompts/ db/ sandbox-services/
```

One `lib/` namespace; Code nodes import from `lib/index.js` or specific modules.

### Sandbox boundaries

All runtime writes stay under `N8N_DATA_ROOT`. HTTP calls allowed only to `http://localhost` mock-api when explicitly enabled. See [[governance/sandbox-boundaries]].

### Simulacrum rule

No production endpoints in POC. Every external integration has an entry in [[integrations/catalog]] plus a simulator under `lib/simulators/` or `sandbox-services/`.

### Schema-first

Normalize inbound artifacts to canonical schemas (`lib/schemas/`) before side effects. Append lifecycle events before external posts (CRM, ticketing, email).

### Prompts in repo

Version prompt templates under `prompts/`; reference by path from lib. No API keys in prompt files.


| Rule | Detail |
|------|--------|
| Workflow JSON in git | Export from editor; review diff like code |
| No secrets in JSON | Remove credential IDs/values before commit; use [[credentials/catalog]] |
| `.n8n/` gitignored | Runtime DB, encryption keys — never commit |
| `credentials/` in git | **Empty** — `.gitkeep` only; local exports gitignored |
| Pin n8n version | README + workflow notes |
| One workflow file per workflow | Name matches vault note `workflows/<name>.md` |

