## Workflow design

### Workflow scope

| Principle | Detail |
|-----------|--------|
| One outcome per workflow | Split unrelated automations |
| Sub-workflows | Use **Execute Workflow** for shared sequences (validation, enrichment, notify) |
| Error workflows | Use **Error Trigger** workflow for centralized alerting/logging when appropriate |
| Size | If canvas exceeds ~15–20 nodes, consider split or sub-workflow |

### Trigger selection

| Use case | Prefer |
|----------|--------|
| External event | Webhook (production URL documented, not committed) |
| Scheduled batch | Schedule Trigger |
| File drop | Local File Trigger (local/sandbox) or polling pattern |
| Manual / demo | Manual Trigger |
| Downstream of another flow | Execute Workflow Trigger |

Document trigger mode and activation requirements in the workflow vault note.

### Node selection (built-in first)

| Task | Prefer | Avoid |
|------|--------|-------|
| Field mapping / rename | **Set** | Code that only copies fields |
| Conditional route | **IF** or **Switch** | Code with if/else chains |
| Multi-rule route | **Switch** | Nested IFs |
| HTTP call | **HTTP Request** | Code `fetch` unless unsupported |
| JSON parse/stringify | **Set** / built-in expressions | Code |
| Merge streams | **Merge** | Code concatenation |
| Loop over items | **Split In Batches** / n8n item model | Manual loops in Code when avoidable |
| Custom domain logic | **lib/** + thin Code, or **custom node** | Large Code blocks |

### Node display names

State intent: `Validate payload`, `Fetch customer`, `Map to CRM shape`.

Avoid defaults: `Code`, `IF`, `HTTP Request1`.

### Sticky notes

Every production workflow: top sticky with purpose + link to vault note `[[workflows/<name>]]`.

### Item model

- Understand **one item = one output row** from upstream nodes.
- Preserve **paired item** metadata when using Merge and sub-workflows where traceability matters.
- Document expected `$json` shape at workflow input in vault note.
- Binary data: document property name; use Move Binary Data / explicit binary handling — do not assume text.

### Expressions

- Use expressions (`{{ }}`) for simple field access and transforms n8n supports natively.
- Extract complex, reused expressions to **Set** node outputs or `lib/` — do not duplicate the same expression in five nodes.

