## Custom community nodes

### INodeType structure

- **`description`** — `displayName`, `name`, `group`, `version`, `inputs`, `outputs`, `properties`, `credentials` (if any).
- **`execute`** — orchestration only; delegate to imported modules.
- **Version** — bump `description.version` on breaking property changes; document in CHANGELOG.

### ICredentialType

- Separate file per credential type.
- `test` request should hit a safe endpoint (sandbox), not production.
- Never log credential values.

### Build and install

```bash
npm install
npm run build          # gulp / tsc per package template
npm link               # local dev into n8n custom nodes directory
```

Document exact steps in [[guides/getting-started]].

### Errors in custom nodes

Use n8n's error types — fail loud with context:

```typescript
import { NodeOperationError } from 'n8n-workflow';

throw new NodeOperationError(this.getNode(), 'orderId is required', {
  itemIndex: i,
});
```

Do not return empty items to mean failure.

