## Happy path and fail fast

### Philosophy

Implement the **correct path** for valid items. Invalid input and operational failures must be **visible** — routed to an error branch, Error Trigger workflow, or thrown error — not dropped silently.

| Situation | Response |
|-----------|----------|
| Invalid input item | IF branch to error output, or throw in Code / `NodeOperationError` |
| HTTP 4xx/5xx | Document: Error branch, Continue On Fail + IF, or stop workflow |
| Missing credential | Fail at configure time; document type in [[credentials/catalog]] |
| Partial batch failure | Split In Batches + document per-item error handling |
| Bug in lib/ | Fix lib/; do not patch only on canvas |

### Continue On Fail

- **Default: off** for nodes where failure must block downstream work.
- If enabled: **must** document in workflow note and handle error output explicitly (IF on `$json.error` or equivalent).
- Never enable globally to "make it work" without an error path.

### Guard validation early

Validate at workflow entry (IF, Filter, or validation sub-workflow) before side effects (HTTP POST, file write, DB).

