## Pre-commit checklist

- [ ] Built-in nodes preferred; Code nodes thin
- [ ] DRY — no duplicated logic across workflows
- [ ] Error paths documented; no silent Continue On Fail
- [ ] No credentials/secrets in diff
- [ ] Node display names + stickies updated
- [ ] Target n8n version noted if nodes changed
- [ ] `npm test` / `.\scripts\run.ps1 test` passes
- [ ] Vault notes + workflow notes updated
- [ ] `git diff` reviewed

---

## Git workflow

```powershell
git status
git diff
.\scripts\run.ps1 test    # or npm test / npm run build
git add <files>
git commit -m "feat: concise message describing why"
git status
```

Commit only when tests pass (where applicable), build succeeds (packages), and docs match artefacts.

